<headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 29 at 8:02AM MDT  by NWS GreatFalls</headline>
<description>...Strong and Gusty Winds Expected through Today...
Westerly winds will continue to increase along the Rocky Mountain
Front through the remainder of the morning, becoming strong and
gusty through the afternoon hours today. Sustained wind speeds of
30 to 40 mph, with gusts approaching 60 mph are expected from the
late morning through afternoon hours today, which will lead to
difficult travel conditions, especially for high profile vehicles
or those pulling trailers. Be prepared for strong cross winds.
Know your vehicles limits and exercise cautions while traveling.</description>
